      },
      "message": "Fix generate_collage.py fallback: emit path, not image_url (#86)\n\nThe designer CLI writes the generated image to a local file and prints the\nfile path on stdout (not a URL). After the CLI rename, the fallback branch\nwas storing that local path under the \"image_url\" key, which callers would\ntry to use as a remote URL.\n\nMatch the sibling make_product_grid.py convention: when the value is a local\npath, use the \"path\" key; reserve \"image_url\" for the primary aimage_generation\npath whose return value is a real URL. Callers must now check both fields.\n\nUpdate outfit-recommendation/SKILL.md Step 7 to document the two return shapes.\n\nCo-authored-by: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
