      "message": "chore: remove obsolete /extra-skills path references from prompts and docs (#84)\n\n* chore: remove obsolete /extra-skills path references from prompts and docs\n\necap-skills have been remounted at ~/.openclaw/skills/ (managed priority\nlevel 3) by fastclaw PR #56, which naturally overrides bundled skills.\nThe old \"Tool Routing Policy (Extra Skills First)\" prompt hack and the\nhardcoded /extra-skills/ path references in docs are no longer needed.\n\nChanges:\n- Remove \"Tool Routing Policy\" section from 5 AGENTS.md files\n  (careerbloom, oura-ring-connector, podcast-pal,\n   restaurant-review-monitor, stylist-agent)\n- Drop Path column from design-researcher/TOOLS.md skill table\n- Replace /extra-skills/<name> text references with skill names in\n  dr-report-builder/SKILL.md, mkt-meta-ads-pro/SKILL.md, stylist-agent/TOOLS.md\n\nOut of scope (follow-up):\n- bash blocks in SKILL.md that invoke `python3 /extra-skills/...`\n- Python scripts with hardcoded subprocess paths\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\n* chore: update subprocess script paths for ecap-skills managed-priority mount\n\nAfter fastclaw PR #56, ecap-skills are mounted at ~/.openclaw/skills/\n(managed priority 3) instead of /extra-skills/. Update the cross-skill\nsubprocess calls in these scripts so they resolve the correct location.\n\nUsing os.path.expanduser('~/...') keeps the code independent of the\ncontainer's HOME user (currently 'node') without hardcoding\n/home/node/.openclaw in sources.\n\nFiles:\n- restaurant-review-monitor/skills/daily-digest/scripts/fetch_yelp.py\n- restaurant-review-monitor/skills/daily-digest/scripts/run_daily.py\n- stylist-agent/skills/outfit-recommendation/scripts/generate_collage.py\n\nRationale for keeping subprocess pattern:\n- run_daily.py and fetch_yelp.py run as an OpenClaw cron job with no\n  LLM in the loop, so \"let the corresponding skill do it\" via agent\n  routing is not applicable. subprocess is the current canonical\n  cron-to-skill invocation mechanism.\n- generate_collage.py's subprocess call is a fallback path only; the\n  primary path uses litellm directly. Rewriting the fallback would\n  change the script's exception-handling contract.\n\nCo-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>\n\n* Revert \"chore: update subprocess script paths for ecap-skills managed-priority mount\"\n\nThis reverts commit eab1244d83013be9a57f73d94d38634d369c3425.\n\n---------\n\nCo-authored-by: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>",
